projects.name: Deep Learning Project Alzeihmers Classification and Detection
projects.description: Developed a deep learning model using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Support Vector Machines (SVM), PCA, and LDA models to classify and detect Alzheimer's disease from brain MRI images. Achieved high accuracy in identifying Alzheimer's patterns, contributing to early diagnosis efforts.

projects.name: Computer Network Project Office Networking on Cisco Packet Tracer
projects.description: Designed and implemented a secure network infrastructure using Cisco Packet Tracer to connect the ACCOUNTS and DELIVERY departments. Implemented Cisco switches and routers, including VLAN setup, IP addressing, and routing protocols to optimize network performance and security for departmental connectivity.

projects.name: Automated Toll Tax System
projects.description: Engineered an automated toll payment system using RFID technology to detect vehicles and deduct tolls from linked accounts, eliminating need for cash transactions. Demonstrated proficiency in RFID systems, IoT devices and traffic management.

projects.name: Password Manager (Database Project)
projects.description: Developed a robust password manager application leveraging SQL databases to securely store and manage user credentials. Designed database schema and implemented SQL queries for efficient retrieval, insertion, and encryption of passwords and associated metadata. Implemented user authentication and access control mechanisms using SQL to ensure data security and confidentiality in compliance with industry standards.

projects.name: Hydroponics and Crop Tracker
projects.description: Designed and built an automated hydroponics system to grow vegetables indoors with no soil. Programmed Arduino to monitor temperature, pH, and humidity in the system. Utilized various sensors to log the data to our servers.
